subSubSection.paragraph:
Head. Mandibular plates with dark lateral stripe. Tylus with dark margin (
Fig. 13A
). ventral surface yellow. First rostral segment surpassing bucculae in lateral view.

Thorax. Pronotum sparsely punctured, punctures coarse (
Fig. 13A
); cicatrices, delimiting furrows and surrounding calloused stripes concolorous with pronotum (
Fig. 13A
), without spots or punctures. Anterolateral margin pale yellow to greenish yellow; line of light brown coarse punctures short, not reaching ¼ of the margin. Scutellum with coarse, large, black punctures sparser on anterior half than on posterior half, posterior punctures fine, dense and black (
Fig. 13A
). Corium with all veins yellow. Propleura with brown stripe alongside brown or concolorous, fine and dense punctures; lateral margin green. Evaporatorium concolorous and slightly rugose with dark spots (
Fig. 13B
). Peritreme long reaching 2/3 of the distance between ostiole of the scent gland and margin of the body. Metasternal process light green with arms broad and receiving fourth rostral segment (
Fig. 13B
).

Abdomen. Connexivum with excavations concolorous, densely punctured only on inner margin; base of lateral spines green. Lateral part of segment VII, corresponding to ventral side of connexivum, greenish yellow with margin black. Spiracles on concolorous area. Small brown rounded spot close to spiracle on each segment (
Fig. 13B
).

Male (
Fig. 7A–C
). Pygophore with posterolateral angles barely flat laterally and slightly projected (
Fig. 7A
). Superior process of the genital cup small and elliptical. Paramere with large anterior process, short and rounded posterior process, and arrow head like basal process; dorsal margin enlarged and sulcated (
Fig. 7B
). Proctiger brown with posterior face yellow, short, not reaching level of posterolateral angles (
Figs 7 A, C
); lateral excavation forming dorsally a small crest; dorsal part of posterior face tumid. Ventral rim medially brown; expansions barely developed and not tumid. Ventral surface mostly green with central suffused dark stripe and median spot; punctures fine and concolorous or light brown (
Fig. 7C
). Phallus long, ventral part large, distal part developed and bitumid (
Fig. 10H
).

Female (
Fig. 7D
). Gonocoxites 8 with lateral margin almost straight and posterior margin slightly curved; punctures concentrated on basal part; sutural border excavated on distal half forming a "U"; internal margin rugose; carina from gonapophysis 8 visible. Gonocoxites 9 narrow, distal part straight; Laterotergites 8 with distal spine black slightly curved; clearly below the level of segment VII. Laterotergites 9 with small part of the base excavated; clearly below the level of laterotergites 8. Capsula seminalis globose, strongly developed; processes bulky and long, clearly exceeding anterior annular flange, increasing in length (
Fig. 11H
). Ductus receptaculi (tdr) shorter than capsula seminalis.
